New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo passed Kareem Abdul-Jabbar for the most double-doubles in Milwaukee Bucks history
Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded a double-double with 25 points, 16 rebounds, and 8 assists in a blowout 121-105 Bucks win
Pre-Game Insights: The match was a high-profile one between two of the best internationals players in the game, Antetokounmpo and Victor Wembanyama
Post-Match Reflections: The Bucks have climbed back into the playoff picture in a pretty winnable Eastern Conference
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks have struggled since their NBA Cup Championship in Las Vegas against the Oklahoma City Thunder but seem to be turning things around
Others: The Bucks are still a formidable team that can score with just about anybody, and Antetokounmpo changes things just enough on defense for the Bucks to be hard to beat in a seven-game series
